import json
from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains
import time
import pyperclip

# Read the input JSON file containing product links
with open('product_links.json', 'r') as f:
    product_links = json.load(f)

# Initialize a Chrome browser
driver = webdriver.Chrome()

# Create a list to store the updated product information
updated_products = []

# Loop through the product links and scrape images
for product in product_links:
    product_url = product['link']
    driver.get("https://www.google.com")
    search_box = driver.find_element_by_name("q")
    search_box.send_keys(product_url)
    search_box.send_keys(Keys.RETURN)
    time.sleep(5)  # Wait for the page to load
    new_url = driver.current_url
    driver.get("https://qc.pandabuy.com/")
    search_input = driver.find_element_by_id("url")
    search_input.send_keys(new_url)
    view_photo_button = driver.find_element_by_id("view-photo")
    view_photo_button.click()
    photo = driver.find_element_by_id("photo")
    action_chains = ActionChains(driver)
    action_chains.context_click(photo).send_keys(Keys.ARROW_DOWN).send_keys(Keys.RETURN).perform()
    image_url = pyperclip.paste()

    # Create an updated product dictionary
    updated_product = {
        "id": product['id'],
        "name": product['name'],
        "category": product['category'],
        "image": image_url,
        "description": product['description'],
        "price": product['price'],
        "link": product_url
    }
    updated_products.append(updated_product)

# Close the browser
driver.quit()

# Write the updated product information to a new JSON file
with open('updated_products.json', 'w') as output_file:
    json.dump(updated_products, output_file, indent=4)

print("Scraping completed. Updated product information saved to 'updated_products.json'.")
